Package com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.broadcast

Primary classes to configure and broadcast a live media stream.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    WZBroadcastAPI.AdaptiveBroadcaster  
    WZBroadcastAPI.AudioBroadcaster  
    WZBroadcastAPI.Broadcaster
    The Broadcaster interface defines the methods that must be implemented by classes developed as broadcast components with instances registered with an instance of the WZBroadcast class via an instance of the WZBroadcastConfig class.
    WZBroadcastAPI.BroadcastErrorCallback
    The BroadcastErrorCallback interface defines the callback method that is invoked by WZBroadcastAPI.Broadcaster classes when an error occurs during a broadcast
    WZBroadcastAPI.VideoBroadcaster  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    WZBroadcast
    The WZBroadcast class is used to configure and control a live streaming broadcast.
    WZBroadcastAPI
    Interfaces for video and audio encoder classes developed to extend the SDK.
    WZBroadcastConfig
    The WZBroadcastConfig class provides configuration properties for a live streaming broadcast
    WZBroadcastStat
    Represents a sample collected during a broadcast session containing network bandwidth measurement statistics
    WZGLBroadcaster
    This class can be used to integrate the GoCoder SDK into an existing application's OpenGL ES-based rendering pipeline to broadcast content from sources other than WZCameraView
    WZH264Broadcaster  

Package com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.broadcast Description

Primary classes to configure and broadcast a live media stream. Additional classes that enable the capture and streaming of content from additional sources such as the output of an OpenGL-based gaming app and external capture devices.
